						<summary>

						<p>In the same place.</p>						

						<p>This inscription is damaged.</p>						

						<p>It records a gift of 2-1/2 <hi rend="italic">mā</hi> of land in Kōḍālakkuḍi as <hi rend="italic">kuḍiṉīṉkāda-dēvadāṉam,</hi> the gift being named as <hi rend="italic">Arumuṉaikaṇḍa-pichchaikkuḍi</hi> to the images of Sundaranāyaṉār and [Pa]ravaināch[chiyār] set up in the temple of Tirumuttīśuram-uḍaiya-nāyaṉār, by a certain Āḍuvāṇḍār Poṉkaṟṟaḷi <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Arumu[ṉai]kaṇḍapich[chaṉ] and his brother who belonged to the <hi rend="italic">Āṇḍār</hi> community and resided in the temple premises. </p>						

						</summary>
